<TITLE> Dhaka hosting 6 day int'l geosciences summit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  A six-day International Conference on Geosciences for Global Development kicked off the capital on Monday, on addressing management of natural, climate change and earthquake disasters among a host of topics. "We will benefit hugely if the conference gives us guidelines about mineral resources management especially coal exploration, climate change and other issues including natural disasters," the prime minister's adviser for energy affairs, Toufique-e-Elahi Chowdhury, said at the launch of the conference at Osmani Hall. Geologists from 35 countries are participating in the conference, organised by the Bangladesh Geographical Society, Geological Survey in Bangladesh, Association of Geosciences for International Development, International Geosciences Education Organisation and International Union of Geographical Science. GSB president Sirajul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com, "The conference will focus on different types of natural disasters including earthquake, flood, draught, and river erosion occurring across the globe, including Bangladesh." On top of that research papers on extraction of natural resources would be presented at the conference, he said. He also said recommendations on these issues would be formulated on the basis of different information presented at the conference. The inauguration of the conference was addressed among others by energy and mineral resource secretary Mohammad Mohsin and IUGS president professor Alberto C.Rikardo b
